<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-17297] Use Yetus before YETUS-994 to enable adding comments to GitHub</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-17297</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/YETUS-994&quot; title=&quot;Add GitHub Status as a report type&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;YETUS-994&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;YETUS-994&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, test-patch updates the commit status instead of adding a comment in GitHub. Use the commit hash before &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/YETUS-994&quot; title=&quot;Add GitHub Status as a report type&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;YETUS-994&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;YETUS-994&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; because of the following reasons:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Yetus feature seems to be broken for now (Trying and debugging in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hadoop/pull/2348&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hadoop/pull/2348&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use the fixed version to avoid surprising the developers&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The latest Yetus version is 0.12.0 but it does not support &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/YETUS-972&quot; title=&quot;Make javadoc phase and goal configurable in maven.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;YETUS-972&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;YETUS-972&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which is required to run javadoc with Java 11.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
